<item>
            <title>[OAK-5357] StringUtils conversion functions can throw NullPointerException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-5357</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;tt&gt;StringUtils&lt;/tt&gt; class in &lt;tt&gt;oak-commons&lt;/tt&gt;, the methods &lt;tt&gt;convertBytesToHex()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;convertHexToBytes()&lt;/tt&gt; can throw NullPointerException if the argument passed in is null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13029580">OAK-5357</key>
            <summary>StringUtils conversion functions can throw NullPointerException</summary>
